SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"At Your Bark'n Call\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/at-your-bark-n-call\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Winchester\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":13,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Audrey's Barkyard\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/audreys-barkyard\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Wake Forest\",\"addressRegion\":\"NC\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":14,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Bag of Bones Barkery\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bag-of-bones-barkery\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Hamilton Township\",\"addressRegion\":\"NJ\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":15,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Baltimore Pet Shoppe\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/baltimore-pet-shoppe\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Philadelphia\",\"addressRegion\":\"PA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":16,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Bar K\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bar-k\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Kansas City\",\"addressRegion\":\"MO\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":17,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Bark & Fly Ranch\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bark-fly-ranch\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"High Point\",\"addressRegion\":\"NC\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":18,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Bark & Meow\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bark-meow\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Yonkers\",\"addressRegion\":\"NY\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":19,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Bark & Ride\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bark-ride\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"San Ramon\",\"addressRegion\":\"CA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":20,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"name\":\"Bark & Zoom\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bark-zoom\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Del Valle\",\"addressRegion\":\"TX\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}}]}}0:{\"buildId\":\"j39O7b4H81jaidut2lEaa\",\"rsc\":[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2\"}}],\"$L3\",\"$L4\",\"$L5\",\"$L6\"],null,\"$L7\"]}],\"loading\":null,\"isPartial\":false}\n3:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"container mx-auto px-4 py-4\",\"style\":{\"position\":\"absolute\",\"top\":\"80px\",\"left\":0,\"right\":0,\"zIndex\":10},\"children\":[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"className\":\"breadcrumb-nav\",\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"breadcrumb-list\",\"style\":{\"display\":\"flex\",\"alignItems\":\"center\",\"gap\":\"0.5rem\",\"listStyle\":\"none\",\"padding\":0,\"margin\":0,\"fontSize\":\"0.875rem\"},\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"className\":\"breadcrumb-item\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L8\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"style\":{\"color\":\"#667eea\",\"textDecoration\":\"none\"},\"children\":\"Home\"}]}],[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"className\":\"breadcrumb-separator\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\",\"style\":{\"color\":\"#9ca3af\"},\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"className\":\"breadcrumb-item breadcrumb-current\",\"aria-current\":\"page\",\"style\":{\"color\":\"#374151\"},\"children\":\"Parks with Bars\"}]]}]}]}]\nb:T83a,A Bark Away NJ in [Jersey City](/cities/jersey-city-nj) offers a versatile and modern approach to canine care, specializing in balanced training programs that seamlessly integrate into the busy lifestyle of urban pet parents. Founded by certified trainer Criselda Quan, this service provides a wide range of options from foundational puppy training to advanced behavior modification. Their philosophy is rooted in a structured and compassionate methodology, aiming to build a common language of trust between dogs and their owners. One of their most unique offerings is the 'Bark Pack Walk,' a three-hour social and educational experience that includes complimentary pick-up and drop-off. These supervised group sessions are designed to provide both physical exercise and mental stimulation, allowing dogs to practice polite leash behavior and social impulse control in a real-world park setting under the guidance of a professional trainer.\n\nFor owners seeking more intensive support, A Bark Away NJ provides immersive 'Board & Train' programs for three to five weeks, focusing on deep-seated behavioral issues and elite-level obedience. They also offer a flexible 'Drop-Off Training' service for busy weekdays, where dogs work on focus and manners at the trainer's location before returning home in the evening. For those who prefer to be directly involved, their 'Bark Home School' and private in-home sessions offer personalized coaching in the dog's own environment, addressing everything from potty training to separation anxiety. The service also includes loving and reliable pet sitting, providing a specialized 'Meet and Greet' to ensure every guest is comfortable before an overnight stay. With a commitment to clear communication and long-term results, A Bark Away NJ delivers a verified, high-touch training solution that transforms the way humans and dogs live together in the Jersey City community. Whether you are looking for a routine of spirited pack walks or seeking a total behavioral overhaul, Criselda's expert team treats every dog with the individualized logic and love they deserve.c:T66f,AJ Country Kennel anchors Lemoore's dog-loving rhythm as a dog park that marries expansive play yards with concierge-level care. Located in Lemoore, CA, the park is tucked near 15800 Idaho Ave, Lemoore, CA 93245 and easy to reach for commuters and weekend adventurers alike. Guests rave about its 4.8-star average across 67 reviews, pointing to spotless grounds, intuitive traffic flow, and staff who remember every pup's quirks. The campus layers mature trees with long sight lines so guardians can relax while still keeping eyes on the action. Morning, afternoon, and twilight blocks are thoughtfully staggered to keep crowds light and vibes relaxed. Drop-in passes, punch cards, and community days keep the experience accessible without sacrificing premium touches.\n\nExpansive turf runs, agility challenges, and shaded rest nooks stretch across the property so dogs can sprint, sniff, and reset without ever feeling crowded. AJ Country Kennel curates small-group play dates, confidence-building agility rotations, and gentle introductions for new rescues. Weekly enrichment labs, pop-up adoption drives, and local vendor markets keep Lemoore's canine calendar fresh. Certified behavior teams circulate through each yard, coaching leash manners and offering quick progress reports. Health-forward protocols guide every visit at AJ Country Kennel, from double-gated entries to staff-monitored hydration breaks. Check http://www.ajcountrykennel.com/ for day passes, vaccination policies, and community spotlights. AJ Country Kennel partners with nearby shelters, trainers, and pet-forward cafes to keep Lemoore's vibrant dog scene moving together.d:T7ba,All American Pet Resorts in [North Brunswick](/cities/north-brunswick-township-nj) provides a premier, all-inclusive 'home away from home' experience, specializing in cage-free boarding and high-energy daycare for dogs of all life stages. Located on Thalia St, this state-of-the-art facility is uniquely staffed by Pet Care Specialists 24/7/365, ensuring that every guest receives constant supervision and expert care even through the night. The resort's flagship accommodations are its spacious, glass-front luxury suites, which completely eliminate the need for cages or crates, providing a transparent and comfortable environment. Guests enjoy advanced climate control and a specialized air purification and exchange HVAC system, along with custom sanitation protocols that maintain an exceptionally healthy and fresh-smelling facility at all times.\n\nThe activity program at All American Pet Resorts is centered on a massive 9,000-square-foot indoor and outdoor play area where dogs are carefully grouped for socialization by breed, size, age, and play style. Every boarding stay is all-inclusive, meaning that professional dry food, fresh raised bedding, daily playtimes, and personal walks are provided at no extra cost. A standout feature of the resort is its 24-hour webcam system, which allows pet owners to check in on their companions from anywhere in the world, providing total transparency and peace of mind. The facility also offers a professional on-site grooming salon, ensuring that every pup can return home looking as refreshed as they feel. With a verified, near-perfect reputation for reliability and a deeply affectionate approach to customer service, All American Pet Resorts North Brunswick delivers an authoritative and essential care solution. Whether your puppy needs a safe place for early socialization or your senior dog requires an attentive holiday stay, the team here treats every guest with the expert logic and individualized love they deserve.e:T422,Serious about your pup's fitness and focus? Angela Hibbard Park in [Brick Township](/cities/brick-township-nj) delivers a top-tier environment designed for activity and engagement. Rated 4.5 stars by a community of 282 disciplined dog owners, this facility is built on the logic of \"constructive play.\" It’s not just about running around; it’s about mental stimulation, clear boundaries, and a structured space where dogs can burn off energy productively.\n\nThe layout at Angela Hibbard Park is ideal for training exercises, recall practice, and agility drills. The grounds are kept in peak condition to ensure safety during high-intensity play, and the respectful community of regulars understands the value of good canine etiquette. Whether you are working on commands or just need a reliable space for vigorous exercise, this facility provides the professional-grade consistency that serious dog owners demand.\n\nFor more details, visit the [official property website](http://www.bricktownship.net/) to learn more about their services and updated hours.f:T66f,Animal Den is the beating heart of Sacramento's canine community, offering a dog park experience tailored to social, curious pups. Located in Sacramento, CA, the park is tucked near 4060 Power Inn Rd, Sacramento, CA 95826 and easy to reach for commuters and weekend adventurers alike. Guests rave about its 4.8-star average across 492 reviews, pointing to spotless grounds, intuitive traffic flow, and staff who remember every pup's quirks. The campus layers mature trees with long sight lines so guardians can relax while still keeping eyes on the action. Morning, afternoon, and twilight blocks are thoughtfully staggered to keep crowds light and vibes relaxed. Access runs on membership memberships, with flexible passes that welcome both spontaneous drop-ins and devoted regulars.\n\nExpansive turf runs, agility challenges, and shaded rest nooks stretch across the property so dogs can sprint, sniff, and reset without ever feeling crowded. Animal Den curates small-group play dates, confidence-building agility rotations, and gentle introductions for new rescues. Weekly enrichment labs, pop-up adoption drives, and local vendor markets keep Sacramento's canine calendar fresh. Certified behavior teams circulate through each yard, coaching leash manners and offering quick progress reports. Health-forward protocols guide every visit at Animal Den, from double-gated entries to staff-monitored hydration breaks. Check http://animaldenpetresort.com/ for day passes, vaccination policies, and community spotlights. Animal Den partners with nearby shelters, trainers, and pet-forward cafes to keep Sacramento's vibrant dog scene moving together.10:T481,If you're looking for the ultimate wag-worthy social hub in [Hamilton Township](/cities/hamilton-township-nj), look no further than Bag of Bones Barkery. This vibrant community destination has earned a reputation as the \"place to be\" for local pet parents who want more than just a walk—they want a meetup. Boasting a solid 4.8-star rating from 409 reviews, the park radiates a welcoming energy where tails never stop wagging and neighbors become friends. Whether you're there for a quick playdate or a long afternoon of socializing, the atmosphere is always buzzing with positivity.\n\nAt Bag of Bones Barkery, the focus is on connection. The layout encourages interaction, making it easy for pups to find playmates while owners chat on the sidelines. It’s not just a facility; it’s a social pillar of the Hamilton Township scene, offering a safe, clean, and joyous environment where every visitor feels like a VIP. For a fun, friendly, and community-centered experience, this spot is a local favorite.\n\nFor more details, visit the [official property website](http://www.bagofbonesbarkery.com/) to learn more about their services and updated hours.11:T878,Located on the vibrant riverfront of Kansas City, Bar K is far more than just a typical dog park—it is a revolutionary community destination that completely reimagines the dog-friendly experience for modern pet owners. This expansive two-acre facility uniquely combines a professionally maintained, fully staffed dog park with a modern bar, restaurant, and event space, creating a one-of-a-kind environment where pups and people can socialize in style. The park features thoughtfully designed separate play areas for large and small dogs, all supervised by trained 'Dogtenders' who actively monitor play to ensure safe and fun interactions for every visitor. Customizable agility courses, climbing structures, and seasonal splash pools keep active dogs entertained for hours, while the climate-controlled indoor spaces provide year-round comfort, ensuring the fun never stops regardless of the unpredictable Missouri weather. Whether you are looking for a place to let your dog burn off excess energy or a spot to relax with a locally brewed craft beer while your furry friend plays nearby, Bar K offers an unparalleled experience that bridges the gap between a dog park and a social club.\n\nBeyond the impressive outdoor play areas, Bar K excels in hospitality, offering a robust experience for both humans and hounds. The on-site restaurant serves a diverse menu of healthy, locally sourced food for pet parents, alongside a dedicated 'Doggie Menu' featuring gourmet treats like beef stew, turkey meatballs, and dog-friendly ice cream. The facility serves as a vibrant hub for social events, regularly hosting adoption drives in partnership with local shelters, live music performances, and even trivia nights, fostering a tight-knit community of dog lovers. With a strong focus on safety, cleanliness, and member satisfaction, Bar K has established itself as a premier destination in the Midwest. Its innovative approach has set a new standard for dog parks across the country. For more information on [membership options](https://barkdogbar.com/) and day passes, or to find other top-rated local favorites, visit [Indoor Dog Park](https://www.indoordogpark.org/).12:T616,Perched in San Ramon, Bark & Ride delivers a dog park experience where energetic romps and mindful training feel perfectly balanced. Located in San Ramon, CA, the park is tucked near Stoneleaf Rd, San Ramon, CA 94582 and easy to reach for commuters and weekend adventurers alike. Guests rave about its 4.5-star average across 77 reviews, pointing to spotless grounds, intuitive traffic flow, and staff who remember every pup's quirks. The campus layers mature trees with long sight lines so guardians can relax while still keeping eyes on the action. Morning, afternoon, and twilight blocks are thoughtfully staggered to keep crowds light and vibes relaxed. Access runs on membership memberships, with flexible passes that welcome both spontaneous drop-ins and devoted regulars.\n\nExpansive turf runs, agility challenges, and shaded rest nooks stretch across the property so dogs can sprint, sniff, and reset without ever feeling crowded. Bark & Ride curates small-group play dates, confidence-building agility rotations, and gentle introductions for new rescues. Weekly enrichment labs, pop-up adoption drives, and local vendor markets keep San Ramon's canine calendar fresh. Certified behavior teams circulate through each yard, coaching leash manners and offering quick progress reports. Health-forward protocols guide every visit at Bark & Ride, from double-gated entries to staff-monitored hydration breaks. Check http://www.ci.san-ramon.ca.us/cms/One.aspx?portalId=10826130&pageId=11693008 for day passes, vaccination policies, and community spotlights.4:[\"$\",\"$9\",null,{\"fallback\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"loading\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-hourglass-split\"}],\" Loading dog parks...\"]}],\"children\":[\"$\",\"$La\",null,{\"initialParks\":[{\"id\":\"ChIJ6wpFntt0TYgR3rb2wfoE-vk\",\"name\":\"A Bark Above Pet Salon\",\"businessType\":\"Dog Park\",\"description\":\"A Bark Above Pet Salon has become a favorite among the area residents.  What makes this dog facility special is its safe, excellent, professional. The staff's dedication to creating a positive experience for both dogs and their owners is evident in every visit. safe environment for my puppy Located in a safe area, This facility specializes in Pet care and Professional services. For more information, call (540) 339-6182. Visit their website at http://abarkabovepet.com/ to learn more about their services and pricing.\",\"slug\":\"a-bark-above-pet-salon\",\"address\":\"2532 Rutrough Rd SE\",\"street\":\"2532 Rutrough Rd SE\",\"city\":\"Roanoke\",\"state\":\"VA\",\"zipCode\":\"24014\",\"full_address\":\"2532 Rutrough Rd SE, Roanoke, VA 24014, USA\",\"latitude\":37.24697079999999,\"longitude\":-79.895499,\"googlePlaceId\":\"ChIJ6wpFntt0TYgR3rb2wfoE-vk\",\"phone\":\"(540) 339-6182\",\"website\":\"http://abarkabovepet.com/\",\"photos\":null,\"rating\":4.3,\"reviewCount\":34,\"openingHours\":{},\"amenities\":{\"Onsite services\":true,\"Indoor facilities\":true,\"Professional staff\":true,\"Climate controlled\":true,\"Wheelchair accessible entrance\":true,\"Parking available\":true,\"Easy access\":true},\"pricing\":{\"pricingSource\":\"website\",\"isFree\":false},\"placeTypes\":[\"point_of_interest\",\"establishment\"],\"lastUpdated\":null,\"dataQuality\":\"verified\",\"photo\":null,\"faqs\":[],\"source\":\"static\",\"listingType\":\"free\"},{\"id\":\"ChIJPQyT8r0kukYROlUb_fJHC4k\",\"name\":\"A Bark Away NJ\",\"businessType\":\"Dog Park\",\"description\":\"$b\",\"slug\":\"a-bark-away-nj\",\"address\":\"311 West Side Ave apt 107\",\"street\":\"311 West Side Ave apt 107\",\"city\":\"Jersey City\",\"state\":\"NJ\",\"zipCode\":\"07305\",\"full_address\":\"311 West Side Ave apt 107, Jersey City, NJ 07305, USA\",\"latitude\":40.7131316,\"longitude\":-74.0905669,\"googlePlaceId\":\"ChIJPQyT8r0kukYROlUb_fJHC4k\",\"phone\":\"(716) 573-6015\",\"website\":\"https://www.abarkawaynj.com/\",\"photos\":null,\"rating\":5,\"reviewCount\":30,\"openingHours\":{\"Monday\":\"9:00 AM – 6:00 PM\",\"Tuesday\":\"9:00 AM – 6:00 PM\",\"Wednesday\":\"9:00 AM – 6:00 PM\",\"Thursday\":\"9:00 AM – 6:00 PM\",\"Friday\":\"9:0